\
\'93I hope his color doesn\'92t run,\'94 Crowell said, \'93before they pay off.\'94\
\
\'93He was really a lovely horse,\'94 Catherine said. \'93I wonder if Mr. Meyers\
backed him.\'94\
\
\'93Did you have the winner?\'94 I called to Meyers. He nodded.\
\
\'93I didn\'92t,\'94 Mrs. Meyers said. \'93Who did you children bet on?\'94\
\
\'93Japalac.\'94\
\
\'93Really? He\'92s thirty-five to one!\'94\
\
\'93We liked his color.\'94\
\
\'93I didn\'92t. I thought he looked seedy. They told me not to back him.\'94\
\
\'93He won\'92t pay much,\'94 Meyers said.\
\
\'93He\'92s marked thirty-five to one in the quotes,\'94 I said.\
\
\'93He won\'92t pay much. At the last minute,\'94 Meyers said, \'93they put a lot of\
money on him.\'94\
\
\'93Who?\'94\
\
\'93Kempton and the boys. You\'92ll see. He won\'92t pay two to one.\'94\
\
\'93Then we won\'92t get three thousand lire,\'94 Catherine said. \'93I don\'92t like\
this crooked racing!\'94\
\
\'93We\'92ll get two hundred lire.\'94\
\
\'93That\'92s nothing. That doesn\'92t do us any good. I thought we were going to\
get three thousand.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s crooked and disgusting,\'94 Ferguson said.\
\
\'93Of course,\'94 said Catherine, \'93if it hadn\'92t been crooked we\'92d never have\
