\
\'93Ask him what he played,\'94 I said to Crowell.\
\
\'93What are you on, Mr. Meyers?\'94 Crowell asked. Meyers took out his\
programme and pointed to the number five with his pencil.\
\
\'93Do you mind if we play him too?\'94 Crowell asked.\
\
\'93Go ahead. Go ahead. But don\'92t tell my wife I gave it to you.\'94\
\
\'93Will you have a drink?\'94 I asked.\
\
\'93No thanks. I never drink.\'94\
\
We put a hundred lire on number five to win and a hundred to place and\
then had another whiskey and soda apiece. I was feeling very good and we\
picked up a couple more Italians, who each had a drink with us, and went\
