\
\'93You have to put up two hundred lire to make twenty,\'94 he said. \'93Twelve\
lire for ten. It\'92s not worth it. My wife lost twenty lire.\'94\
\
\'93I\'92ll go down with you,\'94 Catherine said to me. The Italians all stood\
