\
\'93Do you like this?\'94 Catherine asked.\
\
\'93Yes. I guess I do.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s all right, I suppose,\'94 she said. \'93But, darling, I can\'92t stand to\
see so many people.\'94\
\
\'93We don\'92t see many.\'94\
\
\'93No. But those Meyers and the man from the bank with his wife and\
daughters\'97\'97\'94\
\
\'93He cashes my sight drafts,\'94 I said.\
\
\'93Yes but some one else would if he didn\'92t. Those last four boys were\
awful.\'94\
\
\'93We can stay out here and watch the race from the fence.\'94\
\
\'93That will be lovely. And, darling, let\'92s back a horse we\'92ve never heard\
of and that Mr. Meyers won\'92t be backing.\'94\
\
\'93All right.\'94\
\
We backed a horse named Light For Me that finished fourth in a field of\
five. We leaned on the fence and watched the horses go by, their hoofs\
