\
\'93That wasn\'92t a very big one. I had a very big one a while ago. The\
doctor made me go clear out, didn\'92t you, doctor?\'94 Her voice was strange.\
It rose on the word doctor.\
\
The doctor smiled.\
\
\'93I want it again,\'94 Catherine said. She held the rubber tight to her face\
and breathed fast. I heard her moaning a little. Then she pulled the\
mask away and smiled.\
\
\'93That was a big one,\'94 she said. \'93That was a very big one. Don\'92t you\
worry, darling. You go away. Go have another breakfast.\'94\
\
\'93I\'92ll stay,\'94 I said.\
\
\
\
We had gone to the hospital about three o\'92clock in the morning. At noon\
Catherine was still in the delivery room. The pains had slackened again.\
She looked very tired and worn now but she was still cheerful.\
\
\'93I\'92m not any good, darling,\'94 she said. \'93I\'92m so sorry. I thought I would\
do it very easily. Now\'97there\'92s one\'97\'94 she reached out her hand for the\
mask and held it over her face. The doctor moved the dial and watched\
